    <briefdescription>
<para>Manages state transitions using a rule-based system. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Implements both Manager and <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1TypedStateCommandHandler" kindref="compound">TypedStateCommandHandler</ref> interfaces. Processes state transition commands by matching against registered rules, executing guards, and notifying listeners.</para>
<para>## Transition Flow</para>
<para>1. Commands are submitted via <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1StateManager_1a5dbf046b7fd2a72a339d20fb0ef8f642" kindref="member">submit()</ref> and queued 2. During <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1StateManager_1a9819c7a390fe2e1dc79aa03d3b36268d" kindref="member">flush()</ref>, the last pending command is processed 3. Rules are checked to find a matching transition 4. If a guard is present, it must return true 5. Listeners are notified: onStateExit -&gt; onStateTransition -&gt; onStateEnter 6. Session state is updated</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>StateType</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The state enum type.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1types_1_1StateTransitionRule" kindref="compound">StateTransitionRule</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1StateTransitionListener" kindref="compound">StateTransitionListener</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1commands_1_1StateCommand" kindref="compound">StateCommand</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
